{
  "stem": "1216.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And standing on what was essentially the fourth floor, you could see out over the ghetto walls.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Since it was a 45 city, it had, of course, the barbed wire, but it also had heavy walls like Quebec does, on which grew grass.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But they weren't all that high, and so standing on the fourth floor, you could see out over them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And you didn't really see much, it was open country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But it gave us the idea that there was something out there that was not limited space, limited privacy, too many people, too much noise, too much dust, too much dirt, not enough food.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And so we had all sorts of fantasy games in which we would fly away to wherever we wanted, preferably home, of course.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Because we didn't really know what home was anymore by that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Things-- too many things had happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The last bit of schooling we had was, as I earlier described, with a lot of teacher turnover, a lot of student turnover.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know what a real, honest to goodness, regular school was like.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We also didn't know that a regular school doesn't teach you to lie, naturally.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we talked about it, but we didn't really know what we were saying.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we played.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We played with my doll, also.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Both of us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No he didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He and his brother and his parents went on those fall transports, in fall of '44, and then we talked about their being transported east, or transported to Poland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything was east in Poland, even though it really wasn't, necessarily.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And for the longest time, for the next 40 years, or so, I did not know what had happened to him.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
